{% block bodyContent %}

  <h2 id="spacing-scale">The responsive spacing scale</h2>
  <p>We use a responsive spacing scale which adapts across mobile, tablet, and desktop breakpoints. The values below come from <code>$ofh-space-responsive-scale</code>, so the documentation matches the toolkit source of truth.</p>
  <p>The responsive scale and the legacy static <code>ofh-spacing()</code> helper intentionally diverge after the smaller steps. Use the responsive values for layout and component spacing that should adapt with the viewport.</p>

  {% set items = foundationStyles.spacing.scale %}
  {% set caption = "Responsive spacing scale" %}
  {% set variant = "spacing" %}
  {% include "design-system/styles/_partials/showcase-scale.njk" %}

  <h3 id="spacing-override-classes">Spacing override classes</h3>
  <p>Occasionally, you might need to make minor adjustments like adding spacing or removing it from elements of your design. You can use the responsive spacing override classes for this.</p>

  <h3 id="using-the-override-classes">Using the override classes</h3>
  <p>The spacing override classes are structured to allow you to apply any size of the scale, using margin or padding in any direction.</p>
  <p class="rich-text">For example, <code>ofh-u-margin-10</code> sets a margin of {{ foundationStyles.spacing.byStep['10'].mobile }} on mobile, {{ foundationStyles.spacing.byStep['10'].tablet }} on tablet, and {{ foundationStyles.spacing.byStep['10'].desktop }} on desktop.</p>
  <p class="rich-text">To add padding use <code>-padding</code> instead of <code>-margin</code>.</p>
  <p class="rich-text">If you want to add the margin or padding in a particular direction, add <code>left</code> for left, <code>right</code> for right, <code>top</code> for top, or <code>bottom</code> for bottom. For example, <code>-margin-top</code> will set <code>margin-top</code> and <code>-padding-right</code> will set <code>padding-right</code>. If you do not specify a direction, the margin or padding will be applied to all sides of the element.</p>
  <p class="rich-text">The last part of the class represents the spacing step you want to apply. For example, in <code>ofh-u-margin-10</code>, the <code>-10</code> represents step 10 on the responsive scale.</p>

  <h3 id="spacing-examples" class="ofh-u-padding-top-4">Examples</h3>

  {{ designExample({
    group: "styles",
    item: "spacing",
    type: "default",
    htmlOnly: true
  }) }}

  {{ designExample({
    group: "styles",
    item: "spacing",
